er%20getting%20laid%20off.%3Cp%3EJenna%20Curcio%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-moved-to-italy-new-definition-of-success-better-life-2025-5%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emoved%20to%20Italy%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20work%2C%20but%20about%20two%20years%20later%2C%20I%20learned%20my%20contract%20wouldn't%20be%20renewed.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWithout%20citizenship%20or%20savings%2C%20I%20had%20to%20leave%20the%20life%20I%20was%20starting%20to%20build%20behind.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENow%2C%20I'm%20back%20in%20the%20US%2C%20working%20to%20get%20back%20to%20the%20place%20where%20I%20finally%20felt%20like%20myself.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20really%20thought%20I'd%20live%20in%20Italy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESure%2C%20my%20dad%20was%20from%20there%2C%20but%20we%20weren't%20one%20of%20those%20families%20who%20had%20dual%20citizenship%20or%20spent%20summers%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmistakes-visiting-amalfi-coast-first-time-honeymoon-italy-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20Amalfi%20Coast%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20didn't%20even%20speak%20Italian%20%E2%80%94%20but%20one%20opportunity%20changed%20everything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20over%20a%20month%20after%20my%20dad%20passed%20away%2C%20I'd%20been%20let%20go%20from%20my%20job%20and%20was%20cold-emailing%20brands%20I%20admired%2C%20when%20I%20landed%20a%20marketing%20role%20with%20an%20Italian%20beauty%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20role%20offered%20the%20chance%20to%20relocate%20to%20Italy%2C%20and%20I%20thought%2C%20why%20not%3F%20What%20once%20felt%20like%20a%20distant%20dream%20suddenly%20became%20real%2C%20as%20if%20my%20dad%20was%20guiding%20me%20toward%20this%20new%20chapter%20in%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227a90fece-48d3-4eae-9076-6f743b6c8e84%5C%22%3EI%20slowly%20built%20a%20life%20in%20Italy%2C%20but%20just%20when%20I%20thought%20I%20had%20it%20all%20figured%20out%2C%20I%20lost%20it%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221184%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20view%20outside%20the%20author's%20first%20apartment%20in%20Rome.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6866dacd3d5881a51c1cb34e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22888%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJust%20when%20I%20thought%20I'd%20gotten%20used%20to%20my%20life%20in%20Rome%2C%20I%20had%20to%20leave.%3Cp%3EJenna%20Curcio%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20moved%20in%20July%202022%20and%20spent%20my%20first%20few%20weeks%20in%20Pescara%2C%20Italy%2C%20(where%20the%20company's%20offices%20were%20based)%20getting%20to%20know%20my%20team%20and%20easing%20into%20the%20slower%20pace%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20hot%20afternoons%2C%20we'd%20sometimes%20log%20off%20early%20and%20head%20to%20the%20beach.%20It%20was%20a%20kind%20of%20freedom%20and%20balance%20I'd%20never%20experienced%20at%20work%20before.%20I%20didn't%20feel%20pressured%20to%20always%20be%20online%2C%20there%20weren't%20any%20expectations%20to%20work%20weekends%2C%20and%20my%20creativity%20felt%20fed%20by%20my%20real%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20month%2C%20I%20relocated%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-avoid-crowds-rome-italy-tips-local-tour-guide%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ERome%3C%2Fa%3E.%20With%20little%20to%20no%20in-office%20requirements%2C%20the%20city%20seemed%20like%20a%20great%20fit%20for%20me%20because%20of%20its%20public%20transportation%20system%2C%20international%20connections%2C%20and%20lively%20pace.%20Plus%2C%20if%20I%20needed%20to%20get%20to%20Pescara%2C%20I%20was%20only%20a%20two-hour%20bus%20ride%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiving%20in%20Rome%20felt%20easy%20and%20natural%2C%20like%20I'd%20lived%20there%20in%20another%20life.%20I%20woke%20up%20early%20to%20grab%20treats%20from%20my%20local%20bar%20(what%20the%20Italians%20call%20caf%C3%A9s)%2C%20made%20friends%20with%20my%20neighbors%2C%20and%20learned%20where%20the%20non-touristy%20spots%20were.%20I%20also%20got%20used%20to%20the%20nuances%20of%20daily%20life%20in%20the%20city%2C%20from%20public%20transportation%20strikes%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20strong%20air%20conditioning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20visited%20my%20dad's%20family%20in%20Lombardy%20and%20Calabria%2C%20too.%20It%20was%20incredibly%20grounding%20to%20connect%20with%20relatives%20who%20spoke%20little%20English%20but%20welcomed%20me%20anyway.%20I%20felt%20closer%20to%20him%20than%20ever%20before%2C%20but%20it%20was%20hard%20not%20to%20be%20upset%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20he'd%20never%20taught%20me%20the%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20I'd%20made%20an%20effort%20to%20practice%20speaking%20with%20my%20family%2C%20took%20dozens%20of%20classes%2C%20and%20subscribed%20to%20Babbel%2C%20there%20were%20still%20plenty%20of%20moments%20when%20I%20struggled%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20pace%20of%20conversations%20at%20work%20or%20sound%20competent%20at%20the%20post%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20intimidating%2C%20but%20over%20time%2C%20I%20pushed%20through%20the%20discomfort%2C%20asked%20questions%20when%20I%20was%20unsure%2C%20and%20slowly%20started%20to%20pick%20up%20more%20of%20the%20language.%20Day%20by%20day%2C%20I%20built%20a%20quiet%20resilience%20and%20confidence%20I%20hadn't%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20just%20when%20I%20thought%20I'd%20found%20my%20groove%20%E2%80%94%20I'd%20gotten%20my%20residency%20permit%2C%20was%20seemingly%20thriving%20at%20work%2C%20and%20was%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-stay-connected-maintain-friendships-long-distance-tips-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esettling%20into%20a%20new%20friend%20group%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20I%20learned%20my%20contract%20was%20not%20being%20renewed%20due%20to%20budget%20cuts%2C%20and%20I%20wasn't%20the%20only%20one%20affected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20a%20job%2C%20dual%20