e%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecalling%20an%20experience%20working%20with%20a%20weaving%20cluster%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20used%20to%20have%20our%20meals%20at%20different%20homes%20each%20day.%20However%2C%20one%20particularly%20hot%20summer%20day%2C%20I%20developed%20a%20headache%20and%20lost%20my%20appetite.%20I%20declined%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ealoo%20chole%20puri%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0that%20was%20prepared%20for%20me%20and%20instead%20requested%20the%20same%C2%A0%3Cem%3Echaas%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eroti%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0that%20her%20son%20was%20eating.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3Cem%3EChaas%20roti%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eor%20simply%20buttermilk%20and%20chapati%20is%20often%20made%20during%20the%20summers%20when%20it%20gets%20too%20hot%20to%20cook%20on%20an%20open%20fire%20mud%20stove.%20The%20dish%20is%20simple%2C%20made%20with%20leftover%20dried%20chapati%20bites%20crushed%20into%20a%20bowl%20of%20cold%20buttermilk%20with%20onions%2C%20mint%2C%20green%20chillies%20and%20salt.%20It%20is%20a%20naturally%20cooling%20recipe%20that%20protects%20from%20the%20strong%20gusts%20of%20loo.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20she%20said%20it%20in%20front%20of%20her%20son%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20something%20I%20would%20like%20because%20it%20is%20the%20food%20of%C2%A0%3Cem%3Edehati%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20derogatory%20term%20for%20villagers).%20I%20think%20that%E2%80%99s%20one%20incident%2C%20I%20can%20never%20take%20out%20of%20my%20head%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dipali%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20any%20urban-looking%20person%20asks%20them%20for%20local%20food%2C%20they%E2%80%99ll%20end%20up%20making%C2%A0%3Cem%3Edaal%20bati%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(Lentil%20and%20wheat%20bread%20balls)%2C%20thinking%20that%E2%80%99s%20all%20we%20have%20the%20taste%20for%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20reflects.%20The%20pressure%20to%20conform%20to%20urban%20food%20preferences%20and%20the%20commercialisation%20of%20local%20food%20culture%20was%20evident.%20But%20the%20irony%2C%20